@Node REQUIREMENTS "STCCG.guide/Requirements"
@TOC CONTENT
@prev CONTENT
        @{u}@{b}Requirements@{ub}@{uu}

STCCG.guide should work on any Amiga that has OS 2.1 or higher and has
the amigaguide.library and a viewer for amigaguide-files (e.g. multiview)
Of course, you could also use a text viewer...

To view the pictures linked in the guide you need a viewer (multiview
may be ok), which you have to specify during installation. You may get the
pictures (in GIF-Format) from Deciphers Web-Site.

Due to copyright reasons, the pictures are not part of this guide.

1MB of memory is enough for operation, but more memory is indeed
recommended.

@{" Required libraries " Link LIBRARIES}
@EndNode

@Node LIBRARIES "STCCG.guide/Requirements/Required Libraries"
@Toc REQUIREMENTS

        @{u}@{b}Required Libraries@{ub}@{uu}

The following libraries are necessary for STCCG.guide to operate:

        @{b}amigaguide.library@{ub} version 37 or higher

        @{b}datatypes.library@{ub} version 39 or higher
        For the datatypes reader. To work properly, suitable datatypes are
        needed as well. Some datatypes are included with the system;
        several exist as different kinds of freely distributable software.

@EndNode

